    • Method Detail

      • getName

        java.lang.String getName()
        Returns a short name of this CAL type.
        Returns:
        a short name of this CAL type.

      • getUsed

        int getUsed()
        Returns the number of CALs of this type that have been assigned to users. This number might exceed the result of getTotal() if the server is in a bad state and too many are assigned.
        Returns:
        the number of CALs that have been assigned

      • getMax

        int getMax()
        Returns the maximum number of CALs of this type that could ever be present on this server. If this value is greater than the result of getTotal() then more CALs can be acquired for this server. If the result is -1 then an unlimited number of CALs of this type can be present on this server.
        Returns:
        the maximum number of CALs of this type that could ever be present on this server or -1 if an unlimited number of CALs of this type can be present on this server

      • getTotal

        int getTotal()
        Returns the maximum number of CALs of this type that could be assigned to users without purchasing more. If this number is greater than the result of getUsed() then some CALs are available to be assigned to a user without purchasing any more. If the result is -1 then an unlimited number of CALs of this type can be assigned.
        Returns:
        the total number of CALs that are available to this server or -1 if an unlimited number of CALs of this type can be assigned

      • getFree

        int getFree()
        Returns the number of CALs that have been included in the policy. This is the smallest number of CALs can can be present on the server. If the result is -1 then an unlimited number of CALs of this type have been included in the license policy.
        Returns:
        the number of CALs that are included in the policy or -1 if an unlimited number of CALs of this type have been included in the license policy

      • isCountedInServerLimit

        boolean isCountedInServerLimit()
        Returns true if an assignment of this CAL type is counted towards the the server limit for the maximum number of users. If this method returns false, then a Contributor who has only this CAL assigned will not count towards the maximum number of licensed users for the server.
        Returns:
        true if this CAL type affects the total licensed user count

      • isFunctional

        boolean isFunctional()
        Returns true if this CAL type should only be assigned to functional users.
        Returns:
        true if this CAL type should only be assigned to functional users.

      • isFloating

        boolean isFloating()
        Returns true if this CAL type is a floating CAL type.
        Returns:
        true if this CAL type is a floating CAL type.
